I have already shared how much my kids love Peppa Pig. It's that magical show that I put on and there's....silence! Whenever the kids are rowdy and won't settle down, my husband even knows to put on a Peppa Pig DVD for guaranteed peace and quiet!

They really loved the Christmas DVD but Bubbles has topped even that. I'm not sure why except that maybe they are obsessed with bubbles themselves! It's one of those magical things of childhood that kids adore. I guess it's just as fun to watch a beloved character blow bubbles as it is to do it themselves!

There are twelve "Peppasodes" including the first, Bubbles, for your little Peppa Pig fans to enjoy. You will hear plenty of snorts and laughter from your kids watching this DVD. My kids had already seen most of these episodes on TV but it doesn't stop them from watching them over and over again!

If you have a Peppa Pig fan, Bubble would make a cute stocking stuffer! Add in some bubbles for them and you have a perfect theme!

The DVD works so I guess that is all I can say that does not include my review of the cartoon itself.  My daughter loves Peppa Pig and it is a great show for many reasons.  There are lessons in each episode so children actually do learn social skills and lessons about the world around them.  The episodes are short so it is great to put in a car DVD system.  The only down side is since it is a British cartoon so not be surprised if your kids start saying words with a British accent or use slang like mates, jumble sale, biscuits, and power cut just to name a few.  Peppa Pig and Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood are by far and away the best entertainment for toddlers when it comes to learning lessons without knowing they are actually learning.
